// KNOWN LIMITATION — Phase-2 head-only resolution.
//
// This fixture passes the Phase-2 Bismillah scope checker by design.
// The module's not_scope excludes 'parse_files'; the function below
// invokes 'local_alias()'. The Phase-2 checker compares only the head
// identifier of each call path — 'local_alias' — against the
// not_scope set, and 'local_alias' is not listed.
//
// In a hypothetical Phase-2 source with assignments (which this
// surface does not yet support), an attacker could rebind:
//
//     local_alias = parse_files
//     local_alias()    // would silently bypass not_scope
//
// Catching this requires Phase-3 namespace-aware name resolution:
// the checker would need to track local-binding shadowing and
// resolve every call's true target before comparing against
// not_scope.
//
// This fixture exists to convert that docstring caveat into an
// executable test (Perplexity review item #3, Session 1.1 polish):
// the test ``test_known_limitation_passes_by_design`` asserts that
// the Phase-2 checker accepts this file. If a future Phase-3
// implementation closes the gap, that test will start failing — at
// which point the fixture moves from ``known_limitation/`` to
// ``invalid/`` and the test inverts. The framework's discipline is
// to make limitations auditable; pinning the gap with a fixture is
// the cleanest way.

bismillah Sloppy {
    authority: NAMING_MD
    serves: purpose_hierarchy.truth_over_falsehood
    scope: orchestrate
    not_scope: parse_files
}

fn run() {
    // 'local_alias' is not in not_scope — the head check passes.
    // In a Phase-3 namespace-aware checker, this would require
    // resolving local_alias's binding to detect the evasion.
    local_alias()
}
